         <OBJECT_CONTRACT>
            <TITLE>
               <P>Water Safety Control Measures</P>
            </TITLE>
            <REFERENCE_NUMBER>17/2364/EC</REFERENCE_NUMBER>
            <CPV_MAIN>
               <CPV_CODE CODE="90721000"/>
            </CPV_MAIN>
            <TYPE_CONTRACT CTYPE="SERVICES"/>
            <SHORT_DESCR>
               <P>The NHS wales shared services partnership, hosted by Velindre NHS Trust are acting on behalf of Cardiff and Vale University local health board who are seeking to establish a contract for water safety control measures.</P>
            </SHORT_DESCR>
            <VAL_ESTIMATED_TOTAL CURRENCY="GBP">1500000</VAL_ESTIMATED_TOTAL>
            <NO_LOT_DIVISION/>
            <OBJECT_DESCR ITEM="1">
               <CPV_ADDITIONAL>
                  <CPV_CODE CODE="45232430"/>
               </CPV_ADDITIONAL>
               <CPV_ADDITIONAL>
                  <CPV_CODE CODE="90700000"/>
               </CPV_ADDITIONAL>
               <CPV_ADDITIONAL>
                  <CPV_CODE CODE="90733600"/>
               </CPV_ADDITIONAL>
               <n2016:NUTS CODE="UKL22"/>
               <SHORT_DESCR>
                  <P>Water safety management is a key aspect for the protection of the health of patients, visitors and staff in accordance with UK health and safety law. The health board is seeking a contract to cover all aspects of water safety control management through one supplier to ease the administration process, ensure a consistent approach and improve value for money through economies of scale.</P>
               </SHORT_DESCR>
               <AC_PROCUREMENT_DOC/>
               <DURATION TYPE="MONTH">36</DURATION>
               <RENEWAL/>
               <RENEWAL_DESCR>
                  <P>There will be a 2-year extension option after the 36 months stated in this advert at the sole discretion of the Health Board in annual tranches.</P>
               </RENEWAL_DESCR>
               <NO_ACCEPTED_VARIANTS/>
               <NO_OPTIONS/>
               <NO_EU_PROGR_RELATED/>
            </OBJECT_DESCR>
